<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName LSID="07E4B047-2135-6620-DCEE-E05EEAC386BF" authority="Mannerheim, 1830" authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">Stenus ater Mannerheim, 1830</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 1. Geographical subdivision of Iran modified after Petrov (1955) and 2 - 6 distribution data of Steninae: 2. Dianous and the Stenus alpicola species group: ● Dianous coerulescens korgei, ○ Stenus proprius; 3. Stenus ater species group: ➕ Stenus affaber, ● Stenus ater, △ Stenus hypoproditor, ■ Stenus intricatus zoufali, ● Stenus mongolicus, ○ Stenus nodipes, ▲ Stenus skoraszewskyi; 4. Stenus brunnipes species group: ● Stenus brunnipes brunnipes; 5. Stenus canaliculatus species group: ● Stenus canaliculatus; 6. Stenus cautus species group: ○ Stenus cautus. Abbreviations: C - Caspian wet forest region, D - deserts and salt marshes, G - Golestan region, Gh - Ghohrud Mountains, Hm - mountains of Hormozgan, Khu - Khuzestan Plain, NB - North Baluchestan Mountains, NKh - North Khorasan Mountains, NNW - northern part of North Zagros Mountains, NZ - North Zagros Mountains, SB - South Baluchestan Mountains, SC - coast of Persian Gulf and Oman Sea, SE - southern slopes of Elburz Mountains, SKh - southern Khorasan Mountains, SZ - southern Zagros Mountains in Fars, Z - Zagros Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74428" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, Suppl. material 1
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="chorology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the West Palaearctic and recorded as far east as European Russia, Azerbaijan, and North Iran, where it reaches its eastern limit of distribution in the Turkmeno-Khorasanian Mountains at about 58°06'E (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 1. Geographical subdivision of Iran modified after Petrov (1955) and 2 - 6 distribution data of Steninae: 2. Dianous and the Stenus alpicola species group: ● Dianous coerulescens korgei, ○ Stenus proprius; 3. Stenus ater species group: ➕ Stenus affaber, ● Stenus ater, △ Stenus hypoproditor, ■ Stenus intricatus zoufali, ● Stenus mongolicus, ○ Stenus nodipes, ▲ Stenus skoraszewskyi; 4. Stenus brunnipes species group: ● Stenus brunnipes brunnipes; 5. Stenus canaliculatus species group: ● Stenus canaliculatus; 6. Stenus cautus species group: ○ Stenus cautus. Abbreviations: C - Caspian wet forest region, D - deserts and salt marshes, G - Golestan region, Gh - Ghohrud Mountains, Hm - mountains of Hormozgan, Khu - Khuzestan Plain, NB - North Baluchestan Mountains, NKh - North Khorasan Mountains, NNW - northern part of North Zagros Mountains, NZ - North Zagros Mountains, SB - South Baluchestan Mountains, SC - coast of Persian Gulf and Oman Sea, SE - southern slopes of Elburz Mountains, SKh - southern Khorasan Mountains, SZ - southern Zagros Mountains in Fars, Z - Zagros Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74428" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3</figureCitation>
). Records from Kazakhstan (
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana, A" journalOrPublisher="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="37" pagination="579 - 624" refId="B79" refString="Smetana, A, 2004. Steninae. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Vol. 2: 579 - 624" title="Steninae." volume="Vol. 2" year="2004">Smetana 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 554), which were adopted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuelke, M" journalOrPublisher="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="37" pagination="304 - 900" refId="B77" refString="Schuelke, M, Smetana, A, 2015. Staphylinidae [Omaliinae - Scydmaeninae]. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Vol. 2/1: 304 - 900" title="Staphylinidae [Omaliinae - Scydmaeninae]." volume="Vol. 2 / 1" year="2015">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schülke">Schuelke</normalizedToken>
and Smetana (2015
</bibRefCitation>
: 806), mainly refer to other species and are not reliable (
<bibRefCitation author="Kastcheev, VA" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="437 - 460" refId="B31" refString="Kastcheev, VA, Puthz, V, 2011. Contribution to the knowledge of the fauna of Steninae (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) of the [sic!] Kazakhstan. 319th Contribution to the Knowledge of Steninae. Entomofauna 32: 437 - 460" title="Contribution to the knowledge of the fauna of Steninae (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) of the [sic!] Kazakhstan. 319 th Contribution to the Knowledge of Steninae." volume="32" year="2011">Kastcheev and Puthz 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 454). In Iran, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Towards the east, it is replaced by its close relative 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eppelsheim" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus mongolicus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus mongolicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species occur sympatrically in the eastern Elburz and the Turkmeno-Khorasanian Mountains (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 1. Geographical subdivision of Iran modified after Petrov (1955) and 2 - 6 distribution data of Steninae: 2. Dianous and the Stenus alpicola species group: ● Dianous coerulescens korgei, ○ Stenus proprius; 3. Stenus ater species group: ➕ Stenus affaber, ● Stenus ater, △ Stenus hypoproditor, ■ Stenus intricatus zoufali, ● Stenus mongolicus, ○ Stenus nodipes, ▲ Stenus skoraszewskyi; 4. Stenus brunnipes species group: ● Stenus brunnipes brunnipes; 5. Stenus canaliculatus species group: ● Stenus canaliculatus; 6. Stenus cautus species group: ○ Stenus cautus. Abbreviations: C - Caspian wet forest region, D - deserts and salt marshes, G - Golestan region, Gh - Ghohrud Mountains, Hm - mountains of Hormozgan, Khu - Khuzestan Plain, NB - North Baluchestan Mountains, NKh - North Khorasan Mountains, NNW - northern part of North Zagros Mountains, NZ - North Zagros Mountains, SB - South Baluchestan Mountains, SC - coast of Persian Gulf and Oman Sea, SE - southern slopes of Elburz Mountains, SKh - southern Khorasan Mountains, SZ - southern Zagros Mountains in Fars, Z - Zagros Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74428" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghahari, H" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="1959 - 1968" refId="B22" refString="Ghahari, H, Anlas, S, Sakenin, H, Ostovan, H, Tabari, M, 2009b. A contribution to the rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinoidea: Staphylinidae) of Iranian rice fields and surrounding grasslands. Linzer biologische Beitraege 41 (2): 1959 - 1968" title="A contribution to the rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinoidea: Staphylinidae) of Iranian rice fields and surrounding grasslands." volume="41" year="2009 b">Ghahari et al. (2009b</bibRefCitation>
: 1964) recently published 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Behshahr, Mazandaran, a record which is in accord with the distribution pattern of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
Judging from the vast distribution in the Mediterranean, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus ater" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Stenus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be an expansive Holomediterranean faunal element.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
